block content

  // Article Hero
  header.bg-primary.text-white.py-5(style="margin-top: 76px;")
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8
          nav(aria-label="breadcrumb")
            ol.breadcrumb.mb-3
              li.breadcrumb-item
                a.text-white-50(href="/") Home
              li.breadcrumb-item
                a.text-white-50(href="/blog.html") Blog
              li.breadcrumb-item.active.text-white(aria-current="page") Sober Things to Do
          h1.display-5.fw-bold 20 Sober Things to Do in Spokane, WA – Fun for Every Season
          p.lead.mt-3.text-white-75 Recovery doesn't mean giving up fun. Spokane is packed with incredible sober experiences — here are 20 to get you started.
          .small.text-white-50.mt-2
            i.bi.bi-calendar3.me-1
            | March 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp;
            i.bi.bi-clock.me-1
            | 6 min read

  // Article Body
  section.page-section
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8

          // Intro
          p.lead.mt-5
            | One of the biggest fears people have about getting sober is losing their social life — and that fear makes sense. But here's what nobody tells you: sober life in Spokane can be genuinely, surprisingly, joyfully full. This city has mountains, rivers, world-class running events, art galleries, coffee shops, farmers markets, and a recovery community that knows how to celebrate life. Whether you're brand new to sobriety or years into your journey, these 20 ideas will help you rediscover just how much fun doesn't require a drink.

          hr.my-5

          // Section 1 – Outdoor Adventures
          h2.mt-4
            i.bi.bi-tree.text-primary.me-2
            | 1. Outdoor Adventures
          p Spokane is an outdoor lover's dream, with easy access to rivers, mountains, parks, and trails no matter the season.

          .row.gx-3.gy-3.mt-1
            .col-md-6
              .card.border-0.shadow-sm.h-100(style="border-radius: 10px;")
                .card-body
                  h6.fw-bold
                    i.bi.bi-water.text-primary.me-2
                    | Riverfront Park
                  p.small.mb-0 Walk the falls, ride the historic gondola over Spokane Falls, or catch a summer concert in the park — all completely free.
            .col-md-6
              .card.border-0.shadow-sm.h-100(style="border-radius: 10px;")
                .card-body
                  h6.fw-bold
                    i.bi.bi-bicycle.text-primary.me-2
                    | Centennial Trail
                  p.small.mb-0 A 37-mile paved trail perfect for walking, running, or cycling along the Spokane River from downtown to Coeur d'Alene.
            .col-md-6
              .card.border-0.shadow-sm.h-100(style="border-radius: 10px;")
                .card-body
                  h6.fw-bold
                    i.bi.bi-cloud-snow.text-primary.me-2
                    | Mount Spokane State Park
                  p.small.mb-0 Ski and snowboard in winter, hike and mountain bike in summer. Only 30 minutes from downtown.
            .col-md-6
              .card.border-0.shadow-sm.h-100(style="border-radius: 10px;")
                .card-body
                  h6.fw-bold
                    i.bi.bi-flower1.text-primary.me-2
                    | Manito Park &amp; Gardens
                  p.small.mb-0 Five distinct gardens including a Japanese garden and rose garden — stunning in spring and summer. Free admission always.

          // Section 2 – Arts & Culture
          h2.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-palette.text-primary.me-2
            | 2. Arts &amp; Culture
          p Spokane's arts scene is deeper than most people expect — and seeing it through sober eyes makes the experience that much richer.
          ul
            li
              strong Northwest Museum of Arts &amp; Culture (MAC):
              |  Rotating exhibits covering art, history, and Native American culture. One of the most visited museums in Washington.
            li
              strong First Friday Art Walk:
              |  Every first Friday of the month, galleries and studios across Spokane open their doors for free. Great for meeting creative people.
            li
              strong Spokane Civic Theatre:
              |  Professional community theater productions year-round. Volunteer usher to attend shows for free.
            li
              strong INB Performing Arts Center:
              |  Major touring shows, concerts, and performances. Check the calendar for free or low-cost events.
            li
              strong Spokane Symphony:
              |  Offers community concerts and open rehearsals at significantly reduced prices throughout the season.

          // Section 3 – Community Events
          h2.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-calendar-event.text-primary.me-2
            | 3. Community Events
          p Spokane hosts world-famous events that bring the whole city together — alcohol is never the point.
          ul
            li
              strong Bloomsday (May):
              |  One of the largest road races in the US — 50,000+ runners. Sign up, train with a running club, and cross that finish line.
            li
              strong Hoopfest (June):
              |  The world's largest 3-on-3 basketball tournament. Play in it, volunteer, or just watch. Downtown Spokane transforms for an entire weekend.
            li
              strong Spokane Farmers Market (May–Oct):
              |  Every Wednesday and Saturday downtown. Fresh produce, local food, live music, and friendly faces.
            li
              strong Spokane Pride (June):
              |  A welcoming, inclusive community celebration with a parade, vendors, and live entertainment.
            li
              strong Spokane County Interstate Fair (September):
              |  Rides, live music, food, and exhibits — a classic family-friendly outing.

          // Section 4 – Fitness & Wellness
          h2.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-activity.text-primary.me-2
            | 4. Fitness &amp; Wellness
          p Physical health and recovery are deeply connected. Spokane's fitness community is welcoming and often free or low-cost.
          ul
            li
              strong Spokane Running Club:
              |  Free group runs through the city. Beginner-friendly, no experience required.
            li
              strong Yoga in the Park:
              |  Free community yoga sessions at Riverfront Park and Manito Park during summer months.
            li
              strong Spokane Valley Recreation Centers:
              |  Low-cost drop-in fitness, swimming, and group classes at multiple locations.
            li
              strong Inland NW Hiking:
              |  An active community hiking group with weekly outings ranging from easy to strenuous — check their Facebook group.
            li
              strong YMCA of the Inland Northwest:
              |  Sliding-scale memberships available for those in financial need. Full gym, pool, and group classes.
          .alert.alert-info.mt-3
            i.bi.bi-lightbulb.me-2
            | Exercise is one of the most effective natural mood boosters — and it's free. Even a 20-minute walk can shift how you feel.

          // Section 5 – Volunteer & Give Back
          h2.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-hand-thumbs-up.text-primary.me-2
            | 5. Volunteer &amp; Give Back
          p Giving your time to others in recovery — or to the broader Spokane community — is one of the most fulfilling things you can do in sobriety.
          ul
            li
              strong AA / NA Service Work:
              |  Set up chairs, make coffee, become a group secretary, or lead a meeting. Service is central to the 12-step philosophy for a reason.
            li
              strong Union Gospel Mission:
              |  Volunteer in the kitchen, serve meals, and connect with people who are exactly where you once were.
            li
              strong Second Harvest Food Bank:
              |  Sort and distribute food to thousands of families each week. A grounding, community-centered experience.
            li
              strong Young People in Recovery (YPR):
              |  Volunteer as an advocate or event coordinator for Spokane's young recovery community.
            li
              strong Habitat for Humanity Spokane:
              |  Build homes, build skills, and build friendships — weekend build days are open to all skill levels.

          // Section 6 – Sober Social Spots
          h2.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-cup-hot.text-primary.me-2
            | 6. Sober Social Spots
          p Sometimes you just want to hang out somewhere comfortable. These Spokane spots are naturally low-key and alcohol-free by default.
          ul
            li
              strong Atticus Coffee &amp; Gifts:
              |  A cozy, artsy coffee shop in the South Perry District — great for reading, meeting people, or journaling.
            li
              strong Auntie's Bookstore:
              |  Spokane's beloved independent bookstore. Browse for hours, attend a reading, or join a book club.
            li
              strong Pinball Pete's &amp; Arcade Bars (non-alcohol focus):
              |  Spokane has a growing arcade and board game scene — great for social events that aren't bar-focused.
            li
              strong Spokane Public Library — Central &amp; Branches:
              |  Free community programs, reading rooms, and quiet spaces to decompress and learn.
            li
              strong Rockwood Coffee:
              |  Another beloved neighborhood café known for its welcoming regulars and relaxed atmosphere.

          // Section 7 – Recovery Community Events
          h2.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-people.text-primary.me-2
            | 7. Recovery Community Events
          p The recovery community in Spokane hosts its own lineup of sober social events, celebrations, and meetups throughout the year.
          ul
            li
              strong Recovery Month (September):
              |  Free public events across the city celebrating recovery — walks, rallies, picnics, and speaker panels.
            li
              strong Sober Sports Leagues:
              |  Recreational volleyball, softball, and disc golf leagues run by and for the recovery community.
            li
              strong Speaker Meetings &amp; Step Workshops:
              |  Open to anyone. Inspiring and often unexpectedly entertaining evenings hosted by local AA/NA groups.
            li
              strong Get Sober Spokane Community Events:
              |  We share sober-friendly events and activities curated specifically for the Spokane recovery community.
          p.mt-3
            | Explore all community events and sober activities: &nbsp;
            a(href="https://www.getsoberspokane.com/community-engagement-sober-activities.html") Community &amp; Sober Activities in Spokane →

          hr.my-5

          // Closing CTA
          .card.border-0.shadow.text-center.p-5.mb-4(style="border-radius: 16px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d6efd11 0%, #19875422 100%);")
            i.bi.bi-stars.display-4.text-primary.mb-3
            h3.fw-bold Your Best Life Is Ahead of You
            p.text-muted.mb-4
              | Spokane is a city that rewards the people who show up for it — and sobriety gives you the clarity to actually enjoy it. Join the Get Sober Spokane community for event updates, sober activity ideas, and connection with people who get it.
            .d-flex.flex-wrap.gap-3.justify-content-center
              a.btn.btn-primary.btn-lg(href="/community-engagement-sober-activities.html" onclick="gtag('event', 'resources_click', {event_category: 'engagement', event_label: 'blog_sober_activities_footer'})")
                i.bi.bi-people.me-2
                | Browse Sober Activities &amp; Events
              a.btn.btn-outline-primary.btn-lg(href="/chat.html")
                i.bi.bi-chat-dots.me-2
                | Join the Community Chat
